The FTIR spectra exhibit characteristic bands for the pPD, DsCl and pPDDS moieties on the surface of the C-dots (Fig. 3
                     ). In general, the nanoparticle spectra showed bands associated with asymmetric and symmetrical stretching (v

                        as and v

                        s
                     ), related to CH (2924-2850; 2966-2800; 3057-2792 cm−1) and NH (3329-3213; 3385 and 3211; 3381-3253 cm−1) groups for C-dots prepared from pPD, DsCl and p-PDDS, respectively [33]. The C-dots obtained from DsCl and pPDDS showed the stretching bands attributed to S = O (1037; 1020 cm−1), SO2 (1371 and 1170; 1355 and 1174 cm−1), vS- O (657; 646 cm-1) and vC-S (756; 783 cm−1) of the aliphatic chain, respectively. For the C-dots obtained from pPD and pPDDS there were deformation bands (δ) related to the bonding of aromatic chains δN-H (1508 and 825; 1469 and 788 cm−1) of NH2 inside and outside the plane, respectively, and bands associated with vC = N bond stretching (1600 and 1579 cm-1) [34].
